---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Base title="FastQC (Rust)">

  <section class="section-divider">
    <p class="label">Unofficial community rewrite</p>
    <h1>FastQC, rewritten in Rust</h1>
    <div class="quality-bars"><span class="qb-1"></span><span class="qb-2"></span><span class="qb-3"></span><span class="qb-4"></span><span class="qb-5"></span><span class="qb-6"></span></div>
    <p class="lead">
      An unofficial rewrite of
      <a href="https://github.com/s-andrews/FastQC">FastQC</a>,
      the sequencing QC tool by Simon Andrews at the Babraham Institute.
    </p>
    <p class="lead">
      <strong>Running QC on sequencing data? Use the
      <a href="https://github.com/s-andrews/FastQC">official Java version</a>, not this one.</strong>
    </p>
    <div class="callout">
      <p>
        This rewrite is primarily a development vehicle for
        <a href={`${base}about/strategy/`}>porting improvements back to the canonical tool</a>
        and a Rust crate for folks building in that ecosystem.
        For regular use, you're better off using the official version from
        <a href="https://www.bioinformatics.babraham.ac.uk/projects/fastqc/">Babraham</a>
        or <a href="https://github.com/s-andrews/FastQC">GitHub</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 2.5rem">
      <a href="https://github.com/s-andrews/FastQC" class="btn btn-primary">Official Java FastQC ↗</a>
      <a href="#why" class="btn btn-outline">Why does this exist?</a>
    </div>
    <img
      src={`${base}images/fastqc.png`}
      alt="FastQC report screenshot"
      class="screenshot"
    />
  </section>

  <section id="why" style="margin-bottom: 3rem">
    <h2>OK, but why does this exist?</h2>
    <p style="color: var(--ink-muted); margin-bottom: 1.5rem">
      Valid question..
    </p>
    <div class="grid-2">
      <div>
        <h3 style="margin-top: 0">Upstream contributions</h3>
        <p style="font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--ink-muted)">
          It started off as a "what if.." and turned into more of a sandbox for
          prototyping improvements, that will hopefully get
          <a href={`${base}about/strategy/`}>ported back to the main Java FastQC</a>.
          The goal is to make the canonical tool better, not to replace it or fragment community usage.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 style="margin-top: 0">Rust crate</h3>
        <p style="font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--ink-muted)">
          Published as <a href="https://crates.io/crates/fastqc-rust"><code>fastqc-rust</code></a>
          for developers building bioinformatics tooling in the Rust ecosystem.
          Produces virtually <a href={`${base}about/equivalence/`}>identical output</a>
          to the Java version.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section style="margin-bottom: 3rem">
    <h2>Performance</h2>
    <p style="color: var(--ink-muted); margin-bottom: 0.5rem">
      Single-threaded, one file (7.3 GB Illumina WES). <a href={`${base}about/performance/`}>Full benchmarks</a>.
    </p>
    <p style="color: var(--ink-muted); font-size: 0.875rem; margin-bottom: 1rem">
      Expect this gap to narrow,
      <a href={`${base}about/strategy/`}>most of these speedups are being contributed upstream</a>.
    </p>
    <div class="grid-2">
      <div>
        <h3 class="bench-title">Wall clock time</h3>
        <div class="bench-chart">
          <div class="bench-row">
            <span class="bench-label">Java</span>
            <div class="bench-bar bench-bar-java" style="width: 100%"></div>
            <span class="bench-time">9m 46s</span>
          </div>
          <div class="bench-row">
            <span class="bench-label">Rust</span>
            <div class="bench-bar bench-bar-rust" style="width: 33%"></div>
            <span class="bench-time">3m 13s</span>
            <span class="bench-speedup">3.0x faster</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="bench-title">Peak memory (RSS)</h3>
        <div class="bench-chart">
          <div class="bench-row">
            <span class="bench-label">Java</span>
            <div class="bench-bar bench-bar-java" style="width: 100%"></div>
            <span class="bench-time">444 MB</span>
          </div>
          <div class="bench-row">
            <span class="bench-label">Rust</span>
            <div class="bench-bar bench-bar-rust" style="width: 6.3%"></div>
            <span class="bench-time">28 MB</span>
            <span class="bench-speedup">16x less</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="install" style="margin-bottom: 3rem">
    <h2>Install</h2>
    <div class="grid-2" style="margin-top: 0.5rem">
      <div>
        <h3 style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 0.8125rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; color: var(--ink-muted); margin-top: 0">From crates.io</h3>
        <pre><code>cargo install fastqc-rust</code></pre>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 0.8125rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; color: var(--ink-muted); margin-top: 0">From source</h3>
        <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/ewels/FastQC.git
cd FastQC && cargo build --release</code></pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section style="margin-bottom: 3rem">
    <h2>Usage</h2>
    <pre><code>fastqc sample.fastq.gz                    # single file
fastqc -o results/ *.fastq.gz             # batch with output dir
fastqc -t 4 --format bam aligned.bam      # parallel, BAM input</code></pre>
    <p style="margin-top: 0.75rem; color: var(--ink-muted)">
      The CLI matches the original. See <code>fastqc --help</code> for all options.
    </p>
  </section>

</Base>

<style>
.bench-title {
  font-family: var(--font-body);
  font-size: 0.8125rem;
  font-weight: 600;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  color: var(--ink-muted);
  margin-top: 0;
  margin-bottom: 0.625rem;
}
.bench-row {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 0.75rem;
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
}
.bench-label {
  font-size: 0.8125rem;
  font-weight: 600;
  width: 2.5rem;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  color: var(--ink-muted);
}
.bench-bar {
  height: 1.5rem;
  border-radius: 3px;
  min-width: 4px;
}
.bench-bar-java {
  background: var(--color-java);
}
.bench-bar-rust {
  background: var(--brand-maroon);
}
.bench-time {
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  font-size: 0.8125rem;
  color: var(--ink-muted);
  white-space: nowrap;
  flex-shrink: 0;
}
.bench-speedup {
  font-family: var(--font-heading);
  font-size: 0.875rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--brand-maroon);
  white-space: nowrap;
  flex-shrink: 0;
}
</style>
